text: Frederick Fisher McCulloch (March 5, 1892 – August 11, 1966Hockey deaths - August 1966) was a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He played with the Victoria Aristocrats of the Pacific Coast Hockey Association during the 1915–16 season. Prior to joining the PCHA McCulloch had won the Allan Cup (as Canadian national amateur champions) in 1914 with the Regina Victorias. ==References== Category:1892 births Category:1951 deaths Category:People from Carleton Place Category:Victoria Cougars (1911–1926) players Category:Canadian ice hockey goaltenders
